<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB06247</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT REFORMING THE COUNTRY'S BASIC EDUCATION SYSTEM, AMENDING FOR THE PURPOSE REPUBLIC ACT NO. 10533, OTHERWISE KNOWN AS "THE ENHANCED BASIC EDUCATION ACT OF 2013"</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Proposes to introduce new provisions to reform R.A.No.10533, to emphasize quality over quantity in teaching, prepare K-12 graduates for both employment and higher education, and ensure that the administration of basic education focuses on improving the learning outcomes of students.

Features include the following:
a. emphasis on TVET as a bridge to both employment and higher education;
b. mother tongue-based materials produced in the actual native language of the learner;
c. a workforce development plan to ensure employability in top employers and high-value industries;
d. TVET as the default senior high school option, while maintaining the other tracks as alternatives;
e. courses in senior high school certified as skills by the TVET;
f. creation of a Learning Materials Development Center for textbooks' accuracy and effectiveness;
g. curricular deloading emphasizing  skill-building;
h. encouraging summer internships among senior high school students.

Emphasizes the integration of several skills into the curriculum as follows: global citizenship, innovation and creativity skills, technology skills and interpersonal skills.
</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>SALCEDA, JOEY SARTE</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2020-02-11</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON BASIC EDUCATION AND CULTURE ON 2020-02-17</td></tr></table>